        {
          "title": "Admin apps list is visible after authenticated login",
          "description": "Verify the requested happy path: after Admin authentication, the Apps section is visible. This case requires valid Admin credentials from the Website Credentials store because the inspection did not reach a post-login state.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to http://localhost:5002.\n   Expected: The Admin app loads at http://localhost:5002/ with HTTP status 200.\n\n2. Log in using the stored Website Credentials for the Core Platform Admin app.\n   Expected: Authentication succeeds without exposing credentials in the test report.\n\n3. Navigate to the Admin Apps section using /admin?nav=apps if the app does not automatically land there.\n   Expected: The browser reaches an Admin URL for the Apps section, such as /admin?nav=apps.\n\n4. Verify the Apps launcher or Apps section is visible.\n   Expected: A visible UI element labeled \"Apps\" is present.\n\n5. Verify no loading or error state blocks the apps list area.\n   Expected: The Apps area is ready for review; no visible blocking error or indefinite loading state prevents list verification.",
          "priority": "Critical",
          "type": "Automated",
