        {
          "title": "Create a new application in Admin via keyboard navigation (Accessibility)",
          "description": "Test the end-to-end creation of a new application in the Admin panel, focusing on keyboard navigability and screen reader compatibility for all form elements in the creation modal.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Ensure the user is logged in as 'adminacc' and on the Apps panel (e.g., URL is 'https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps').\n   Expected: The Apps panel is visible and active.\n\n2. Press the 'Tab' key repeatedly until the 'New' button (for creating a new app) is focused, then press 'Enter'.\n   Expected: A modal titled 'New App' (or similar) appears and receives keyboard focus. Screen reader announces the modal title.\n\n3. Press 'Tab' to navigate to the 'Label' input field. Enter 'A11y Test App {timestamp}' (where {timestamp} is a unique identifier like current time).\n   Expected: The 'Label' field is populated, and screen reader announces the input and its value. The field is correctly identified as a required field if applicable.\n\n4. Press 'Tab' to navigate to the 'API Name' input field. Verify it auto-populated based on the label (e.g., 'a11y_test_app_{timestamp}'). Modify if necessary to ensure it is valid.\n   Expected: The 'API Name' field is correctly auto-populated and editable. Screen reader announces the field and its value.\n\n5. Press 'Tab' to navigate through all remaining input fields and controls within the modal, ensuring each element receives focus in a logical order.\n   Expected: All interactive elements (e.g., Icon picker, descriptions, 'Cancel' button) within the modal are keyboard-focusable and their roles/labels are announced by a screen reader.\n\n6. Press 'Tab' until the 'Create' button is focused, then press 'Enter'.\n   Expected: The 'New App' modal closes successfully. No validation errors are displayed. Screen reader announces the modal closure or context change.\n\n7. Verify that the newly created app ('A11y Test App {timestamp}') appears in the list of applications on the Apps panel.\n   Expected: The application list refreshes, and 'A11y Test App {timestamp}' is visible in the table/list, confirming successful creation and accessibility of the flow.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Ensure the user is logged in as 'adminacc' and on the Apps panel (e.g., URL is 'https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps').\n   Expected: The Apps panel is visible and active.\n\n2. Press the 'Tab' key repeatedly until the 'New' button (for creating a new app) is focused, then press 'Enter'.\n   Expected: A modal titled 'New App' (or similar) appears and receives keyboard focus. Screen reader announces the modal title.\n\n3. Press 'Tab' to navigate to the 'Label' input field. Enter 'A11y Test App {timestamp}' (where {timestamp} is a unique identifier like current time).\n   Expected: The 'Label' field is populated, and screen reader announces the input and its value. The field is correctly identified as a required field if applicable.\n\n4. Press 'Tab' to navigate to the 'API Name' input field. Verify it auto-populated based on the label (e.g., 'a11y_test_app_{timestamp}'). Modify if necessary to ensure it is valid.\n   Expected: The 'API Name' field is correctly auto-populated and editable. Screen reader announces the field and its value.\n\n5. Press 'Tab' to navigate through all remaining input fields and controls within the modal, ensuring each element receives focus in a logical order.\n   Expected: All interactive elements (e.g., Icon picker, descriptions, 'Cancel' button) within the modal are keyboard-focusable and their roles/labels are announced by a screen reader.\n\n6. Press 'Tab' until the 'Create' button is focused, then press 'Enter'.\n   Expected: The 'New App' modal closes successfully. No validation errors are displayed. Screen reader announces the modal closure or context change.\n\n7. Verify that the newly created app ('A11y Test App {timestamp}') appears in the list of applications on the Apps panel.\n   Expected: The application list refreshes, and 'A11y Test App {timestamp}' is visible in the table/list, confirming successful creation and accessibility of the flow.",
