            "test_cases": [
              {
                "title": "Admin list view refresh, search, settings, and export controls remain stable in reachable Apps context",
                "description": "Admin list view refresh, search, settings, and export controls remain stable in reachable Apps context\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin.\n   Expected: Admin entry point loads successfully.\n\n2. If prompted, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\", then click the relevant sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: Authentication succeeds using the exact supplied credentials.\n\n3. Continue to the inspected Admin target and confirm the URL includes ?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.\n   Expected: The Apps panel for selected appId app21vhj4w is the active reachable context.\n\n4. Wait for the Apps list view to settle, then verify no persistent loading indicator or error message remains.\n   Expected: The list view is ready for interaction.\n\n5. Click Refresh in the shared list toolbar.\n   Expected: The list reloads and returns to a stable table/list/grid or empty-state without duplicate rows, broken controls, or error state.\n\n6. Use the list search box with a short query based on visible row/header text when rows exist.\n   Expected: The list filters or returns a valid no-results/empty-state while preserving headers and toolbar controls.\n\n7. Open Settings from the list toolbar.\n   Expected: A modal or settings panel opens with list-view configuration sections such as Columns, Filters, Sort, or Sharing where supported.\n\n8. Close Settings with Cancel or the close control.\n   Expected: The user returns to the Apps list view and the previous list state remains stable.\n\n9. Click Export CSV or Export PDF if enabled.\n   Expected: Export action starts or downloads successfully, or a permission/availability message is shown without breaking the list view.",
                "priority": "Medium",
                "type": "Manual",
                "tags": [
                  "@sanity",
                  "@regression",
                  "@ui",
                  "@positive"
                ],
                "steps": [
                  {
                    "action": "Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin.",
                    "expected": "Admin entry point loads successfully."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "If prompted, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\", then click the relevant sign-in/login control.",
                    "expected": "Authentication succeeds using the exact supplied credentials."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Continue to the inspected Admin target and confirm the URL includes ?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.",
                    "expected": "The Apps panel for selected appId app21vhj4w is the active reachable context."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Wait for the Apps list view to settle, then verify no persistent loading indicator or error message remains.",
                    "expected": "The list view is ready for interaction."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Click Refresh in the shared list toolbar.",
                    "expected": "The list reloads and returns to a stable table/list/grid or empty-state without duplicate rows, broken controls, or error state."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Use the list search box with a short query based on visible row/header text when rows exist.",
                    "expected": "The list filters or returns a valid no-results/empty-state while preserving headers and toolbar controls."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Open Settings from the list toolbar.",
                    "expected": "A modal or settings panel opens with list-view configuration sections such as Columns, Filters, Sort, or Sharing where supported."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Close Settings with Cancel or the close control.",
                    "expected": "The user returns to the Apps list view and the previous list state remains stable."
                  },
                  {
                    "action": "Click Export CSV or Export PDF if enabled.",
                    "expected": "Export action starts or downloads successfully, or a permission/availability message is shown without breaking the list view."
                  }
                ],
                "captureEvidence": true,
                "existingCaseId": "TC-7112-2",
                "reused": true
              },
              {
                "title": "Admin Apps list view loads after login and exposes shared list controls",
                "description": "Admin Apps list view loads after login and exposes shared list controls\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin.\n   Expected: Admin login page or authenticated Admin app is displayed without a browser/network error.\n\n2. If login is shown, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\".\n   Expected: Both credential fields contain the exact supplied values.\n\n3. Click the relevant sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: Login succeeds and the Admin app continues to the inspected target context.\n\n4. Verify the browser URL becomes or remains https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.\n   Expected: User is authenticated and lands in the Admin Apps context for selected appId app21vhj4w.\n\n5. Verify the shared Admin list view container is visible in the Apps panel.\n   Expected: A table/list/grid-style region is present for Apps, or a valid empty-state is displayed if no rows are available.\n\n6. Verify common shared list controls are present where supported: New, Refresh, Export CSV, Export PDF, Summary, Settings, search box, and list-view selector.\n   Expected: Available controls render without overlap and unavailable controls are not shown as broken placeholders.\n\n7. Verify the list view is not stuck in a loading state and does not show an application error state.\n   Expected: No persistent spinner, failed fetch message, blank white page, or RFC-7807 error is visible after the page settles.\n\n8. If rows are present, verify column headers and at least one row render; if no rows are present, verify the empty-state text is visible and actionable controls remain usable.\n   Expected: The Apps list view has a coherent data presentation with headers plus rows, or a clear empty-state with no layout breakage.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin.\n   Expected: Admin login page or authenticated Admin app is displayed without a browser/network error.\n\n2. If login is shown, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\".\n   Expected: Both credential fields contain the exact supplied values.\n\n3. Click the relevant sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: Login succeeds and the Admin app continues to the inspected target context.\n\n4. Verify the browser URL becomes or remains https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.\n   Expected: User is authenticated and lands in the Admin Apps context for selected appId app21vhj4w.\n\n5. Verify the shared Admin list view container is visible in the Apps panel.\n   Expected: A table/list/grid-style region is present for Apps, or a valid empty-state is displayed if no rows are available.\n\n6. Verify common shared list controls are present where supported: New, Refresh, Export CSV, Export PDF, Summary, Settings, search box, and list-view selector.\n   Expected: Available controls render without overlap and unavailable controls are not shown as broken placeholders.\n\n7. Verify the list view is not stuck in a loading state and does not show an application error state.\n   Expected: No persistent spinner, failed fetch message, blank white page, or RFC-7807 error is visible after the page settles.\n\n8. If rows are present, verify column headers and at least one row render; if no rows are present, verify the empty-state text is visible and actionable controls remain usable.\n   Expected: The Apps list view has a coherent data presentation with headers plus rows, or a clear empty-state with no layout breakage.",
