                "description": "Confirms the 'Apps' list view in the Admin panel correctly displays an empty state or 'no results found' message when searching for an application that does not exist.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Ensure the user is currently viewing the 'Apps' list view in the Admin application (e.g., URL `https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps`).\n   Expected: The 'Apps' list view is displayed with existing applications.\n\n2. Locate the search or filter input field within the 'Apps' list view and enter a unique, non-existent app name (e.g., 'NonExistentApp123xyz').\n   Expected: The list view updates to filter results based on the search query.\n\n3. Verify that no application records are displayed in the list view after applying the search filter.\n   Expected: The list view is empty, showing no rows of data.\n\n4. Verify the presence of a 'No results found' or similar empty state message.\n   Expected: A clear message indicating that no items match the search criteria is displayed to the user.",
