        {
          "title": "Admin apps list remains scoped to documented Apps navigation after login",
          "description": "Verify that the Apps view is reached through the documented Admin navigation key and that the visible apps list target is not confused with unrelated Admin sections. This is grounded in the URL-driven Admin navigation contract.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to http://localhost:5002 and authenticate using the stored Website Credentials for the Core Platform Admin app.\n   Expected: The authenticated Admin session is established without embedding secrets in the test.\n\n2. Navigate to /admin?nav=apps.\n   Expected: The Admin single-page app switches to the Apps section.\n\n3. Verify a visible element labeled \"Apps\" is present in the current view.\n   Expected: The Apps launcher or Apps section label is visible.\n\n4. Verify the current view is not one of the other documented Admin sections such as objects, tabs, roles, users, permissions, or audit_logs.\n   Expected: The URL or active navigation state remains scoped to nav=apps.\n\n5. Confirm the view is ready for list verification.\n   Expected: No visible blocking error state prevents the Apps list from being reviewed.",
          "priority": "Medium",
          "type": "Automated",
          "tags": [
            "@ui",
            "@positive"
          ],
          "steps": [
            {
              "action": "Navigate to http://localhost:5002 and authenticate using the stored Website Credentials for the Core Platform Admin app.",
              "expected": "The authenticated Admin session is established without embedding secrets in the test."
            },
            {
              "action": "Navigate to /admin?nav=apps.",
              "expected": "The Admin single-page app switches to the Apps section."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify a visible element labeled \"Apps\" is present in the current view.",
              "expected": "The Apps launcher or Apps section label is visible."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify the current view is not one of the other documented Admin sections such as objects, tabs, roles, users, permissions, or audit_logs.",
              "expected": "The URL or active navigation state remains scoped to nav=apps."
            },
            {
              "action": "Confirm the view is ready for list verification.",
              "expected": "No visible blocking error state prevents the Apps list from being reviewed."
            }
          ],
          "captureEvidence": true,
          "existingCaseId": "TC-505D-5",
          "reused": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Verify 'Apps' List View Displays Empty State for Non-Existent Search",
          "description": "Confirms the 'Apps' list view in the Admin panel correctly displays an empty state or 'no results found' message when searching for an application that does not exist.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Ensure the user is currently viewing the 'Apps' list view in the Admin application (e.g., URL `https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps`).\n   Expected: The 'Apps' list view is displayed with existing applications.\n\n2. Locate the search or filter input field within the 'Apps' list view and enter a unique, non-existent app name (e.g., 'NonExistentApp123xyz').\n   Expected: The list view updates to filter results based on the search query.\n\n3. Verify that no application records are displayed in the list view after applying the search filter.\n   Expected: The list view is empty, showing no rows of data.\n\n4. Verify the presence of a 'No results found' or similar empty state message.\n   Expected: A clear message indicating that no items match the search criteria is displayed to the user.",
          "priority": "High",
          "type": "Automated",
          "tags": [
            "@regression",
            "@admin",
            "@listview",
            "@negative",
            "@search"
          ],
          "steps": [
            {
              "action": "Ensure the user is currently viewing the 'Apps' list view in the Admin application (e.g., URL `https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps`).",
              "expected": "The 'Apps' list view is displayed with existing applications."
            },
            {
              "action": "Locate the search or filter input field within the 'Apps' list view and enter a unique, non-existent app name (e.g., 'NonExistentApp123xyz').",
              "expected": "The list view updates to filter results based on the search query."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify that no application records are displayed in the list view after applying the search filter.",
              "expected": "The list view is empty, showing no rows of data."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify the presence of a 'No results found' or similar empty state message.",
              "expected": "A clear message indicating that no items match the search criteria is displayed to the user."
            }
          ],
          "captureEvidence": true,
          "existingCaseId": "TC-6902-2",
          "reused": true
        },
