                "title": "Accessibility check for Admin-created app visibility path in Keystone",
                "description": "Accessibility check for Admin-created app visibility path in Keystone\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Open https://ops.acchindra.com/shockwave.\n   Expected: Keystone application loads or shows the login screen.\n\n2. If login is shown, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\", then click the sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: User is authenticated and lands on https://ops.acchindra.com/shockwave/.\n\n3. Using only the keyboard, tab through the reachable post-login page controls.\n   Expected: Every reachable interactive control has a visible focus indicator and focus order does not get trapped.\n\n4. If the Keystone app launcher is visible, open it using keyboard interaction and search for the Admin-created app name.\n   Expected: The launcher can be reached and operated by keyboard; the created app result is visible to the admin user.\n\n5. Verify any visible search field or login field has an accessible label or clear programmatic name.\n   Expected: Screen-reader users can identify the purpose of each reachable input.\n\n6. Verify no persistent loading or error state prevents keyboard users from reaching the app launcher; if no visible controls render, log the same blocked condition found during inspection.\n   Expected: Accessibility validation either passes for reachable controls or records the post-login rendering blocker without inventing unavailable UI targets.",
