        {
          "title": "Admin Apps list view loads after login and exposes shared list controls",
          "description": "Admin Apps list view loads after login and exposes shared list controls\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin.\n   Expected: Admin login page or authenticated Admin app is displayed without a browser/network error.\n\n2. If login is shown, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\".\n   Expected: Both credential fields contain the exact supplied values.\n\n3. Click the relevant sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: Login succeeds and the Admin app continues to the inspected target context.\n\n4. Verify the browser URL becomes or remains https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.\n   Expected: User is authenticated and lands in the Admin Apps context for selected appId app21vhj4w.\n\n5. Verify the shared Admin list view container is visible in the Apps panel.\n   Expected: A table/list/grid-style region is present for Apps, or a valid empty-state is displayed if no rows are available.\n\n6. Verify common shared list controls are present where supported: New, Refresh, Export CSV, Export PDF, Summary, Settings, search box, and list-view selector.\n   Expected: Available controls render without overlap and unavailable controls are not shown as broken placeholders.\n\n7. Verify the list view is not stuck in a loading state and does not show an application error state.\n   Expected: No persistent spinner, failed fetch message, blank white page, or RFC-7807 error is visible after the page settles.\n\n8. If rows are present, verify column headers and at least one row render; if no rows are present, verify the empty-state text is visible and actionable controls remain usable.\n   Expected: The Apps list view has a coherent data presentation with headers plus rows, or a clear empty-state with no layout breakage.",
          "priority": "Medium",
          "type": "Manual",
          "tags": [
            "@bvt",
            "@smoke",
            "@ui",
            "@positive"
          ],
          "steps": [
            {
              "action": "Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin.",
              "expected": "Admin login page or authenticated Admin app is displayed without a browser/network error."
            },
            {
              "action": "If login is shown, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\".",
              "expected": "Both credential fields contain the exact supplied values."
            },
            {
              "action": "Click the relevant sign-in/login control.",
              "expected": "Login succeeds and the Admin app continues to the inspected target context."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify the browser URL becomes or remains https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.",
              "expected": "User is authenticated and lands in the Admin Apps context for selected appId app21vhj4w."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify the shared Admin list view container is visible in the Apps panel.",
              "expected": "A table/list/grid-style region is present for Apps, or a valid empty-state is displayed if no rows are available."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify common shared list controls are present where supported: New, Refresh, Export CSV, Export PDF, Summary, Settings, search box, and list-view selector.",
              "expected": "Available controls render without overlap and unavailable controls are not shown as broken placeholders."
            },
            {
              "action": "Verify the list view is not stuck in a loading state and does not show an application error state.",
              "expected": "No persistent spinner, failed fetch message, blank white page, or RFC-7807 error is visible after the page settles."
            },
            {
              "action": "If rows are present, verify column headers and at least one row render; if no rows are present, verify the empty-state text is visible and actionable controls remain usable.",
              "expected": "The Apps list view has a coherent data presentation with headers plus rows, or a clear empty-state with no layout breakage."
            }
          ],
          "captureEvidence": true,
          "existingCaseId": "TC-7112-1",
          "reused": true
        },
        {
          "title": "Admin list view accessibility and keyboard operability in inspected Apps context",
          "description": "Admin list view accessibility and keyboard operability in inspected Apps context\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin and, when prompted, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\", then click the relevant sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: The authenticated Admin experience loads.\n\n2. Navigate to or confirm the inspected target URL https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.\n   Expected: The Apps context is active and stable.\n\n3. Use only the keyboard to move focus through visible interactive elements in the Admin list-view area using Tab and Shift+Tab.\n   Expected: Every visible interactive control receives a clear focus indicator in a logical order, with no keyboard trap.\n\n4. If a table/list/grid is visible, inspect its accessible structure with screen-reader-compatible semantics or accessibility tree tooling.\n   Expected: The data-view exposes an accessible name or context, column/header information, and row or empty-state content that can be perceived without relying only on visual layout.\n\n5. If search, Refresh, Settings, export, or New controls are visible, verify each has an accessible name matching its purpose.\n   Expected: Controls are announced with meaningful names and states; icon-only controls are not unnamed.\n\n6. Check the rendered Apps context for blocking accessibility failures after load.\n   Expected: No critical accessibility violations are present, including missing control names, invisible focus, inaccessible empty-state, or content hidden from assistive technology. If the page remains blank as inspection observed, record the failure as an accessibility blocker because no navigable content is available.\n\nTest Steps:\n\n1. Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin and, when prompted, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\", then click the relevant sign-in/login control.\n   Expected: The authenticated Admin experience loads.\n\n2. Navigate to or confirm the inspected target URL https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.\n   Expected: The Apps context is active and stable.\n\n3. Use only the keyboard to move focus through visible interactive elements in the Admin list-view area using Tab and Shift+Tab.\n   Expected: Every visible interactive control receives a clear focus indicator in a logical order, with no keyboard trap.\n\n4. If a table/list/grid is visible, inspect its accessible structure with screen-reader-compatible semantics or accessibility tree tooling.\n   Expected: The data-view exposes an accessible name or context, column/header information, and row or empty-state content that can be perceived without relying only on visual layout.\n\n5. If search, Refresh, Settings, export, or New controls are visible, verify each has an accessible name matching its purpose.\n   Expected: Controls are announced with meaningful names and states; icon-only controls are not unnamed.\n\n6. Check the rendered Apps context for blocking accessibility failures after load.\n   Expected: No critical accessibility violations are present, including missing control names, invisible focus, inaccessible empty-state, or content hidden from assistive technology. If the page remains blank as inspection observed, record the failure as an accessibility blocker because no navigable content is available.",
          "priority": "Medium",
          "type": "Manual",
          "tags": [
            "@a11y",
            "@regression",
            "@ui",
            "@positive"
          ],
          "steps": [
            {
              "action": "Navigate to https://ops.acchindra.com/admin and, when prompted, enter username/email \"adminacc\" and password \"adminacc@2026\", then click the relevant sign-in/login control.",
              "expected": "The authenticated Admin experience loads."
            },
            {
              "action": "Navigate to or confirm the inspected target URL https://ops.acchindra.com/admin/?nav=apps&appId=app21vhj4w.",
              "expected": "The Apps context is active and stable."
            },
            {
              "action": "Use only the keyboard to move focus through visible interactive elements in the Admin list-view area using Tab and Shift+Tab.",
              "expected": "Every visible interactive control receives a clear focus indicator in a logical order, with no keyboard trap."
            },
            {
              "action": "If a table/list/grid is visible, inspect its accessible structure with screen-reader-compatible semantics or accessibility tree tooling.",
              "expected": "The data-view exposes an accessible name or context, column/header information, and row or empty-state content that can be perceived without relying only on visual layout."
            },
            {
              "action": "If search, Refresh, Settings, export, or New controls are visible, verify each has an accessible name matching its purpose.",
              "expected": "Controls are announced with meaningful names and states; icon-only controls are not unnamed."
            },
            {
              "action": "Check the rendered Apps context for blocking accessibility failures after load.",
              "expected": "No critical accessibility violations are present, including missing control names, invisible focus, inaccessible empty-state, or content hidden from assistive technology. If the page remains blank as inspection observed, record the failure as an accessibility blocker because no navigable content is available."
            }
          ],
          "captureEvidence": true,
          "existingCaseId": "TC-C51C-6",
          "reused": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
